1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with monitoring multiple video streams and detecting interesting objects or activities, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed probabilistic framework to model observer's attentive behavior can be considered as an AI technique. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The foraging strategy proposed in the paper can be seen as a machine learning approach to optimize the observer's attention. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with multiple video streams and video summarization, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes a framework to model human attention, which can be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction.
